question: 濃度
sourceMnemonic:
The <kanji>thickness</kanji> <kanji>degree</kanji> of something is its <vocabulary>density</vocabulary> or <vocabulary>concentration</vocabulary>. After all, the thicker something is, the more dense or concentrated it is.

This word refers to the density or concentration of a mixture or solution, rather than how closely packed something is.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
